WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.300
[Amit Varma]: Do you care about public policy? Your answer to that is probably going to be, no man, policy

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:14.180
[Amit Varma]: is boring. Who wants to be a wonk? What difference does it even make? Fair enough. So let me

00:00:14.180 --> 00:00:19.120
[Amit Varma]: ask you another question. Are you a concerned citizen who cares about society and your own

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:24.080
[Amit Varma]: well-being? If your answer is yes, then you should care about public policy. Public policy

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:30.080
[Amit Varma]: is the things that a government does that impacts your life in a million unseen ways.

00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:34.120
[Amit Varma]: Indeed, my contention is that we would have been a richer country, a better country with

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:39.960
[Amit Varma]: a more humane society, if only we had gotten our public policy right from day one. But

00:00:39.960 --> 00:00:44.040
[Amit Varma]: we didn't. Now, when we look around us and see all that is wrong, what options do we

00:00:44.040 --> 00:00:48.600
[Amit Varma]: have? The majority will make the rational choice of just being silent, getting on with

00:00:48.600 --> 00:00:53.080
[Amit Varma]: their lives, not sweating what they cannot control. Some of us will make a noise, will

00:00:53.080 --> 00:00:58.280
[Amit Varma]: rant, will raise our voice against injustice. But that often amounts to contributing a millionth

00:00:58.280 --> 00:01:04.280
[Amit Varma]: of a decibel in a discourse full of noise. And some of the some of us, a small minority,

00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:09.760
[Amit Varma]: will say, I want to actually find a way of making a difference. And often that way will

00:01:09.760 --> 00:01:18.160
[Amit Varma]: lie through studying and understanding and influencing public policy.

