03:23:42.440 --> 03:23:46.920
[Guest]: So it has not ossified to the extent that other disciplines have.

03:23:46.920 --> 03:23:52.800
[Guest]: So for example, if you are probably applying as an economist, people will tell you that

03:23:52.800 --> 03:23:56.040
[Guest]: you need to have a PhD in economics.

03:23:56.040 --> 03:23:58.120
[Guest]: But that's not the case in public policy.

03:23:58.120 --> 03:24:04.240
[Guest]: So we've had many people who after doing GCPP have gone on to work in governments or taken

03:24:04.240 --> 03:24:10.360
[Guest]: up journalism jobs or taken up jobs with other companies in public policy departments.

03:24:10.360 --> 03:24:14.560
[Guest]: So it's not that you need a master's tag or anything.

03:24:14.560 --> 03:24:18.680
[Guest]: It's more about the learning and the skill set that you develop, not the degree that

03:24:18.680 --> 03:24:19.680
[Guest]: you get.

03:24:19.680 --> 03:24:24.560
[Guest]: So if you can write well, if you can reason well, if you have a broad understanding of

03:24:24.560 --> 03:24:32.520
[Guest]: many disciplines, then a lot of people I see are willing to hire people in this area, right?

03:24:32.520 --> 03:24:35.280
