03:24:35.280 --> 03:24:38.400
[Amit Varma]: Well, like you said, I guess the newness of the discipline helps.

03:24:38.400 --> 03:24:42.960
[Amit Varma]: But as a general question, not about public policy per se, would it be fair to say that

03:24:42.960 --> 03:24:46.440
[Amit Varma]: there is a tradeoff between formal education and self-taught?

03:24:46.440 --> 03:24:51.000
[Amit Varma]: And the tradeoff is that the danger of a formal education is that, like you said, you get

03:24:51.000 --> 03:24:56.080
[Amit Varma]: ossified in certain ways of thinking and can't think beyond that, and might even get tied

03:24:56.080 --> 03:25:00.880
[Amit Varma]: to an ideology or, you know, be incentivized to follow whatever is the academic fashion

03:25:00.880 --> 03:25:03.240
[Amit Varma]: of the day, which is a negative side.

03:25:03.240 --> 03:25:09.080
[Amit Varma]: But the positive side is that you get a systematic exposure to different frames of thinking,

03:25:09.080 --> 03:25:13.960
[Amit Varma]: that you become a part of a community of peers who are also experts in that subject, and

03:25:13.960 --> 03:25:15.800
[Amit Varma]: you learn and grow from that.

03:25:15.800 --> 03:25:20.320
